{
  "doc_id": "55244",
  "text": "As far as 1992 the limiting threshold of ∼ 0.1 J/cm 2 was reported for fullerene solutions, using 8-ns pulses at 532 nm [CITATION_1] . Today's representative values of limiting threshold in various composite materials providing nonlinear absorption or nonlinear scattering are still in the range 0.1-1 J/cm 2 under nanosecond pulses for visible and near-infrared radiation [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Moreover, most studies deal with solutions, while for practical applications rather solid forms are desirable.",
